responded: The vulnerability is in the following code fragment in `Modules/_cursesmodule.c`:

```c
3257|     if (initialised) {
3258|         wrefresh(stdscr);
3259|         return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
3260|     }
```

If `initialised` is true, the code calls `wrefresh(stdscr);` and `PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);`. If `stdscr` is unexpectedly `NULL` (which can happen if `initscr` previously failed or was not called correctly), this will cause a null dereference.

**Patch Solution:**  
Add a check to ensure `stdscr` is not `NULL` before dereferencing it. If it is `NULL`, raise an appropriate Python exception and return `NULL`.

