Since `initscr()` is supposed to initialize `stdscr`, but the crash persists at `wrefresh(stdscr)` and potentially again after `initscr()`, it is possible that in some error circumstances, `initscr()` either returns NULL or fails to initialize the global `stdscr`, leaving it NULL.

